        <section id="deps-spr">
            <h>specifier</h>
            <p>Like other common nouns, <g>bòrd</g> can occur with a <a href="?xx=nouns/determiners"
                    >determiner</a> as pre-specifier.</p>
            <p>Examples with the <a href="?xx=nouns/definite_article">definite article</a> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Dé tha anns <m>a’ bhocsa</m> sin? Tha uighean anns <m>a’ bhocsa</m>.
                            Càit a bheil <m>am bocsa</m>? Tha <m>am bocsa</m> air a’ bhòrd. Có chuir
                                <m>am bocsa</m> air a’ bhòrd? Chuir Màiri.</gd>
                        <tr>What is in that box? There are eggs in the box. Where is the box? The
                            box is on the table. Who put the box on the table? Mary did.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                    </li>
                <li>
                    <gd>Nach robh leabhar anns <m>a’ bhocsa</m> sin? Bha, bha Bìobull ann.</gd>
                    <tr>Wasn’t there a book in that box? Yes, there was a Bible (in it).</tr>
                    <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
