            </xl>
            </p>-->
        </section>
        <section id="uses-obj">
            <h>object</h>
            <p>Like other nouns, <g>bocsa</g> can be used as the object of a transitive verb.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                <li>
                    <gd>Có chuir
                        am <m>bocsa</m> air a’ bhòrd? Chuir Màiri.</gd>
                    <tr>Who put the box on the table? Mary did.</tr>
                    <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                </li>
            </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="uses-comp">
            <h>complement</h>
            <p>Like other nouns, <g>bocsa</g> can be used as the complement of a <a
                    href="?xx=prepositions/prepositions">preposition</a>.</p>
            <p>Examples with <g><a href="?gd=an^preposition">ann am</a> bocsa</g>
                <en>in a box</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Dé tha <m>anns a’ bhocsa sin</m>? Tha uighean <m>anns a’
                            bhocsa</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>What is in that box? There are eggs in the box.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Nach robh leabhar <m>anns a’ bhocsa sin</m>? Bha, bha Bìobull ann.</gd>
                        <tr>Wasn’t there a book in that box? Yes, there was a Bible (in it).</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>




